===Nebraska=== {{Linescore Amfootball| |Road=Nebraska |R1=0||R2=7||R3=0||R4=0 |Home='''Penn State''' |H1=0||H2=13||H3=20||H4=7 }}
In front of a crowd of 110,753, a new [[Beaver Stadium]] attendance record, Penn State routed the [[2002 Nebraska Cornhuskers football team|Cornhuskers]] 40â7, as [[Larry Johnson (American football)|Larry Johnson]] and backup quarterback [[Michael Robinson (American football)|Michael Robinson]] each had two touchdown runs. Cornerback [[Rich Gardner]] had his first career interception and returned it 44 yards for a touchdown in the third quarter. It was Penn State's first victory over a top 10 team since 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gopsusports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/091502aad.html|title=Penn State Dominates Nebraska 40â7, Jump to #15 in ESPN Poll|date=2002-09-15|accessdate=2008-10-28|publisher=Penn State Intercollegiate Athletics}}</ref>
