===Louisiana Tech=== {{Linescore Amfootball| |Road=Louisiana Tech |R1=10||R2=0||R3=7||R4=0 |Home='''Penn State''' |H1=14||H2=7||H3=28||H4=0 }}
Penn State beat the {{cfb link|year=2002|team=Louisiana Tech Bulldogs|title=Bulldogs}} 49â17, despite Tech's quarterback [[Luke McCown]] throwing for more than 400 yards but also threw three interceptions and had a fumble lost. [[Larry Johnson (American football)|Larry Johnson]] ran for 147 yards on 17 carries and two touchdowns and also had a touchdown reception. [[Michael Robinson (American football)|Michael Robinson]] also had three rushing touchdowns.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gopsusports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/092102aac.html|title=Penn State Tames Bulldogs 49â17, Improves to 3â0|date=2002-09-21|accessdate=2008-10-28|publisher=Penn State Intercollegiate Athletics}}</ref>
