[[Larry Johnson (American football)|Larry Johnson]] set Penn State's single-game rushing record as the Nittany Lions shut out the {{cfb link|year=2002|team=Northwestern Wildcats|title=Wildcats}} 49â0. Johnson rushed for 257 yards on 23 carries and scored twice before sitting out the final 28 minutes. In all, twelve Penn State players carried the ball for a total of 423 yards. The defense recorded its first shutout since the 1999 [[Alamo Bowl]], holding the Wildcats to 9 yards rushing and 202 total yards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gopsusports.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/101902aab.html|title=Lions Celebrate 83rd Homecoming with 49â0 Shutout of Northwestern|date=2002-10-19|accessdate=2008-10-28|publisher=Penn State Intercollegiate Athletics}}</ref>
