===Instant replay=== A few other conference coaches had lobbied for instant replay before, but they had fallen on deaf ears until [[Joe Paterno]], who had been against instant replay citing the length of games as a factor, changed his opinion after a number of questionable officiating calls in the Iowa and Michigan games. Paterno and Penn State athletic director Tim Curley called for a comprehensive review of Big Ten officiating. At the news conference after the Michigan game, Paterno went further and said that the conference should change the way that officials are assigned, referring to the assignment of the officiating crew that worked the Michigan game, three of whom live in the state of Michigan.<ref name="officiating">{{cite web|url=http://www.signonsandiego.com/sports/college_football/20021015-1555-fbc-pennst-paterno.html|title=Paterno wants further review of Big Ten officiating practices|last=Lewerenz|first=Dan|publisher=San Diego Union-Tribune|date=2002-10-15|accessdate=2007-01-23}}</ref>
After the Big Ten concluded its comprehensive review of its officiating, the conference implemented a pilot program during the 2003 season to evaluate the use of [[Instant Replay|instant replay]]. The pilot was used to gather data and did not interfere with games or overturn any missed calls.<ref name="replaypilot">{{cite web|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/sports/notebooks/20030815bigten0815p1.asp|title=Big Ten to experiment with program for instant replay|last=Fittipaldo|first=Ray|publisher=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|date=2003-08-15|accessdate=2007-01-23}}</ref>
For the 2004 season, the Big Ten introduced college football's first instant replay system. A technical advisor in the press box with access to the television feeds will be able to stop a game for a replay review and potentially overturn a play, with no limit on the number of plays that can be reviewed.<ref name="replay">{{cite web|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/04218/356960.stm|title=Instant replay comes to Big Ten for a one-year look|last=Fittipaldo|first=Ray|publisher=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|date=2004-08-04|accessdate=2007-01-23}}</ref>
